11. e3 Rd8
{ We will now go for a typical Schara Gambit setup but with our queen on c7 instead. }
12. Qc2 { 12.Be2  was not yet possible due to  12...Bh3  . } 12... Nc6 13. Be2
Ne5
{ A typical move for the Schara Gambit, as the knight on f3 is an important defender. We do, however, never really intend to swap off on f3 but want to keep the tension for now. }
14. O-O Bb6
{ This move pins the c3-knight, which is quite annoying for White. If White ever takes on e5 we can play Qxe5 followed by Bc7 creating threats against White's king. Rac8 is also a useful move here, and sometimes we can play Nfg4 threatening Nxf3+ and Qxh2#. }
