10. O-O a6 { Kicking away the bishop to free up our own light-squared bishop. }
11. Be2 Be6
{ With a very fine IQP position for Black. White is not really able to achieve the b3-Bb2 they want, and we intend to play O-O next followed by Re8 and Rc8 with an active position. The d5-pawn is not weak and White does not have such a good grip on the d4 square either. }
