6. a3 dxc4
{ As stated before, allowing dxc4 followed by b5 is not the way to go for White. Anyway, 6. a3 is a popular move in this position, probably because after @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp3ppp/4pn2/2pp4/2PP4/2N1PN2/PP3PPP/R1BQKB1R b KQkq - 2 5@@EndFEN@@  5...Nc6  the move  6.a3  is also popular. In that position, however, dxc4 followed by b5 is not a threat. We are likely to get positions which are similar to the Queen's Gambit Accepted here, but ones in which the knight on c3 is misplaced. }
