{ Wesley So chose  13.e3  in his game against Grischuk, but to me  13.Nf3  also seems like an interesting alternative, and probably a better move. Having already spend 4 minutes on 10. Rd1, Wesley was clearly out of his notes here. }
13... Nb4
{ The normal way of continuing the initiative in these lines. The threat of Nc2+ is quite annoying for White to deal with.   Instead of this, the alternative  13...Be6  can also be considered. After  14.Nf3  we transpose back to our notes of 13.Nf3 Be6 14.e3.   On top of that,  13...Bf5  could be considered as well. After  14.Bb5  @@StartBracket@@stopping Nb4@@EndBracket@@  14...Rad8  15.Rxd8  Rxd8  16.Nge2  a6  17.Bxc6  Nxc6  we have full compensation as well, with our rook about to join the action on d2 and our bishop coming to d3. }
14. Qa4 Bf5
{ Again,  14...Be6  could be considered, after which White should transpose to our notes of 13. Nf3 by playing  15.Nf3  . }
15. e4
{ The only way of preventing Nc2+, but this is not a good sign for White. It is much better to have the pawn on e3, as it keeps control of the dark squares. }
15... Be6
{ As we have seen before, we have created the idea of playing Nxa2 followed by Bb3 with this move. }
16. a3 Na2 17. Nxa2 Bxa2
{ 17...Qxb2  was also an interesting alternative, but I think the way the game went was also pretty succesful for Grischuk. }
18. Qb4
{ An improvement over So-Grischuk. We can make a draw here with  18...Qc7  19.Qd6  Qa5+  20.Qb4  Qc7  , go for the endgame with @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/pp2npp1/1q6/6p1/1Q2P3/P7/bP3PPP/3RKBNR b K - 1 18@@EndFEN@@  18...Qxb4+  or play  18...Qe6  . All options are 0.00 according to the machine. }
18... Qxb4+
{ 18...Qe6  19.Rd6  Qe5  20.Qd4  Qa5+  21.Qc3  Qa4  22.Rd4  Qe8  leads to a messy position after our queen was being chased for a long time. With Nc6 incoming, we have at least enough compensation for equality. The endgame is the easier option, with plenty of play for the pawn as well. }
19. axb4 Nc6 20. b5 Nb4
{ White is still lacking a ton of development, and with Bb3 or Rfd8 coming we still have a nice initiative going on the queenside. White will face a tough task in this endgame. }
