9. e4 h6 10. Bf4
{ 10.Qg3  could now have been met with  10...Bd6  . After  11.Qxg7  Be5  White can still save the queen with  12.Bf4!  However, after  12...Bxf4  13.Qxh8  O-O-O  Black's initiative is devastating, and only an exchange has been sacrificed.   With  10.Bf4  White seems to able to force a queen exchange. However, as we will see more often in the Schara Gambit, we can still have great compensation in the endgame. }
10... hxg5 11. Bxc7 Rc8 12. Bg3 Nf6
{ With ample compensation for the sacrificed pawn. We have plenty of ideas here. First of all we can soon win the bishop pair with Nh5. The pawn on g5 is restricting White's pieces, and we can consider pushing it to g4 to restrict White even more. Our bishop can come to b4. }
