11. Bxf6 Qxf6
{ The queen on f6 is targetting c3, but it is not as powerful as it could have been on a5. Rxc3 threatens to win the game on the spot now, so White has to react. }
12. Bxa6
{ 12...Rxc3  has now been prevented, as White simply plays  13.Qxb4  . That means that we are forced to play  12...Bxc3+  . }
12... Bxc3+ 13. bxc3 Qxa6
{ This is another useful aspect of Qxf6: the queen was protecting the knight. On a6 the queen is quite annoying for White as it stops White from castling for now. Apart from that, we also have a bishop vs knight, and White's pawn structure has been damaged. We definitely have at least full compensation here. }
