{ 15...Bb4 would not have been a good move this time, but we have to compare @@StartFEN@@2rqkb1r/pp1b1ppp/8/8/8/2nBPN2/P1Q2PPP/R1B2RK1 w k - 0 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Nd4  to  15.Bb2  to understand that. After  15.Bb2  we play  15...Bb4  16.Qb3  a5  , when  17.a3?  loses to  17...Ba4  . This time however, after @@StartFEN@@2rqkb1r/pp1b1ppp/8/8/8/2nBPN2/P1Q2PPP/R1B2RK1 w k - 0 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Nd4  Bb4  16.Qb3  a5  17.a3  Ba4  , White can play  18.Qb2  with a great position, as all of our minor pieces are misplaced.It turns out that the bishop is fine on e7 as well, and we are just intending to castle next. }
16. Qb3 Na4 { Preventing White from grabbing a pawn due to Nc5. } 17. Be2 Nc5
