{ Bxh7 is still a possible move, so we can't castle yet as it would give up  h7  with check. Now for example,  18.Bxh7  can be met with  18...g6  winning the bishop. With the queen on e7  19.Bxg6+  fxg6  20.Qxg6+  Kd8  can be played and is just really good for Black.   Apart from that we intend to meet  18.Qb3  with  18...Qb4  . }
18. Qb3 Qb4 { We do not mind to enter an endgame due to our bishop pair. } 19.
Qd5 { Still preventing us from castling. } 19... Rc5 20. Qd6 Rc8
