21. Qg3
{ This is one way to continue to fight on, but it does not give us problems at all. }
21... O-O 22. Rb1 Qa5 23. Rxb7 Qd5
{ This wins back the pawn, but  23...Bc6  is also fine. In general the bishop pair should give very good play in such open positions, something that we have seen more often in this chapter. After  23...Qd5  play could continue with, for example,  24.Ba6  Qxa2  25.Rxd7  Qxa6  with a balanced position. }
