{ Some calculation needs to be done to make sure this move works, but it does. If you would like to avoid the sharp lines that we will be seeing here I would recommend to have a look at @@StartFEN@@2r1k2r/3bqpbp/p4np1/1pn5/1P6/2N1PN2/P1QBBPPP/R2R2K1 b k - 0 16@@EndFEN@@  16...Nce4  after which play likely continues with  17.Rac1  O-O  18.Qb3  Nxd2  19.Nxd2  with full compensation for the pawn due to the powerful bishop pair. }
