20. Bd3 Bg4 { We are trying to get White to weaken their king with f3. } 21.
Re1 Qd6
{ It is a lot more difficult for White to keep protecting the d4-pawn now that we have lured their bishop to d3 and rook to e1. }
22. Be3 Be6
{ Followed by either Ng4 or Nd5, with a lot of activity compensating for the isolated pawn. }
