Nf6+
{ White would always like to take the bishop with the knight instead of the pawn as this way White creates an escape square for the king on f3. }
21... Kh8
{ We should not put the king on g7 as that would allow a double check with Nh5 or Ne8 in certain positions. }
22. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Bringing the knight back into the game with tempo, as  23.Nxc6  leads to  23...Qd2#  .   22...Qxa1+  23.Ke2  Nb3  actually just transposes to 21. Nxd4 @@StartBracket@@see the variation@@EndBracket@@, so you might consider skipping these lines. However, 22...Nc6 does force the draw here. }
