{ 16.Ra1  now repeats the position. White can still keep the game going with  16.Nc3  or  16.Nxf6+  , but those tries should not lead to an advantage. }
16. Nxf6+ Kg7
{ Driving the knight to h5 is a good idea, as White may get mating threats on h7 if we leave the knight on f6. }
17. Nh5+ Kh8 18. Qc1 Qxa3
{ Qc3+ and Qxc5 were pretty big threats, but we can stop both with this move. }
