{ The material is equal in this endgame, and White should probably not take on b7 with  20.Rxb7  as that will give us a nice initiative after  20...Nd7  or  20...Rc8  . Instead, something like @@StartFEN@@rn3r1k/pp3p1p/8/7N/b7/b3PN2/5PPP/1R2KB1R w K - 0 20@@EndFEN@@  20.Bb5  should be played, but after  20...Bc2  21.Ra1  Bb4+  22.Ke2  a5  play seems to be roughly equal. We can follow up with either Nc6 or Na6. }
