20... Rd8
{ Trading one pair of rooks is quite important in this position.  20...h5  or  20...h6  is also possible, but I quite like this approach of trading one pair of rooks. We mainly do this as White's two rooks could become quite powerful together. The position remains unclear as the material is unbalanced, but roughly equal. }
