{ 13...Rad8  was played in Salem-Tari, but usually the a8-rook should not go to d8. The typical setup is Rac8 and then either Rfd8 or Rfe8. Without a rook on c8, the queen will become too comfortable on c2. }
14. Qb3
{ The queen is quite safe on b3, except for that it can be attacked with Be6. White will meet it with Qc2, and now b5 is not possible anymore. }
14... Be6 15. Qc2 Bg4
{ We intend to take on f3, weakening White's pawn structure on the kingside. Afterwards we can try to go after White's king with Qe5-Qg5/Qh5 or Qd7-Qh3. After  16.Nxe5  we just take back with  16...Qxe5  with an active position. Rfd8 is also quite a useful move here. }
